=== TEST 15: CPU Timing / delay() Calibration ===

--- A: delay() accuracy ---
Calling delay(N), measuring with BIOS tick counter (55ms/tick).

  delay(   1 ms):   0 BIOS ticks = ~0 ms  (expect ~1 ms)
  delay(  10 ms):   0 BIOS ticks = ~0 ms  (expect ~10 ms)
  delay(  55 ms):   1 BIOS ticks = ~55 ms  (expect ~55 ms)
  delay( 100 ms):   2 BIOS ticks = ~110 ms  (expect ~100 ms)
  delay( 500 ms):   9 BIOS ticks = ~495 ms  (expect ~500 ms)
  delay(1000 ms):  19 BIOS ticks = ~1045 ms  (expect ~1000 ms)

--- B: BIOS tick rate ---
Counting BIOS ticks over 1 second (delay-measured).
  1000ms delay = 18 ticks (expect ~18)
  Tick rate OK.

--- C: CPU busy-loop speed ---
  Loops in 1 BIOS tick (~55ms): 2328569
  => Fast CPU (P3+ class)

--- D: I/O port access timing ---
100 sequential inportb() calls, timed with BIOS tick.
  inportb(0x80) calls in 55ms: 87364
  => ~629 ns per I/O read

--- E: outportb() pair timing (8254 low+high byte) ---
The 8254 needs TWO consecutive writes (lo, hi). If an interrupt
fires between them, the counter gets a corrupted value.
  outportb() pairs in 55ms: 20021
  => ~2747 ns per write pair

